NOTE: You may like to create a backup of this folder before starting!

1. SET ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
In order to run the example you need to make sure that you have set the environment
appropriately. You will need to make sure that you edit the variables with values 
starting with REPLACE_WITH_: 
On Linux you need to edit:
	$BLACKTIE_BIN_DIR/setenv.sh
On Windows:
	%BLACKTIE_BIN_DIR%\setenv.bat
Then, execute the script setenv

On Windows: 
You MUST use an environment configured with the VC++ development tools, e.g. launch:
C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio 9.0\VC\vcvarsall.bat


2. RUN THE SERVER
Follow the instructions in $BLACKTIE_BIN_DIR/examples/xatmi/fooapp to start a server  


3. CREATE THE CLIENT
On Linux:
	$BLACKTIE_BIN_DIR/bin/generate_client.sh -Dclient.includes=client.cxx
On Windows:
	%BLACKTIE_BIN_DIR%\bin\generate_client.bat -Dclient.includes=client.cxx


4 RUN THE CLIENT
./client
NOTE: If you get the following error you have not sourced setenv.sh|bat
./client: error while loading shared libraries: libTAO_CosNaming.so.1.6.7: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory